{"type":"message","id":"a4a5d5e9","parentId":"8fee7ce3","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:49:38.864Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Mon 2026-03-23 19:49 EDT] [Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: Build a React web app for Bobby's AI Agent Mission Control dashboard. Design aesthetic: iOS 26 liquid glass / frosted glass — translucent panels, backdrop-blur, soft glows, dark background, clean Apple-like UI.\n\nTech stack: React + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS + Vercel deployment.\n\nDesign specs:\n- Dark background (#0a0a0f or similar very dark)\n- Frosted glass panels: semi-transparent white/dark with backdrop-blur, subtle white border with low opacity, soft glow/shadow\n- Agent cards showing: avatar emoji, agent name, status indicator (green=online, yellow=busy, red=error, gray=offline), last active time\n- Smooth animations and hover effects\n- Mobile responsive\n\nFeatures for Phase 1 (build this now):\n- Grid of agent cards for all 9 agents: dean/main, emmy, x, finn, yoyos, rex, dj, cody, martha\n- Status pulled from OpenClaw gateway (http://localhost:18789 or the LAN address)\n- Click on an agent card to open a compose modal to send them a message\n- Agent list with status indicators\n- Header with title \"Mission Control\" and date/time\n\nRead the OpenClaw docs at /opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs for gateway API endpoints for getting agent status and sessions.\n\nIMPORTANT: Write SPEC.md first, then build the app. Use a clean project structure. Make it look impressive and polished — this needs to match the iOS 26 liquid glass aesthetic described above.\n\nOutput the full project in /Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/"}],"timestamp":1774309778863}}
