{"type":"message","id":"bd078f8a","parentId":"3e114586","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:56:53.806Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The build is clean. Let me now provide a summary of what was built.","thinkingSignature":"ea5528721023bcf630f1689e789c05d63007960a19836890ce4529deebd9a6b6"},{"type":"text","text":"The Mission Control dashboard is built and ready. Here's what was created:\n\n**Project: `/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control/`**\n\n**What was built:**\n- **React + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS** app with iOS 26 liquid glass aesthetic\n- **9 agent cards** (Dean, Emmy, Agent X, Finn, YoYo, Rex, DJ, Cody, Martha) with emoji avatars, status badges (online/busy/error/offline), and last-active timestamps\n- **Gateway integration** via WebSocket (`ws://localhost:18789`) for real-time presence + HTTP polling fallback every 5s\n- **Compose modal** — click any agent to open a frosted-glass modal and send them a message via the gateway's `message` tool\n- **Live clock** in the header (HH:mm:ss + date), gateway connection status indicator\n- **Skeleton loading** state, **toast notifications** on send success/failure\n- **Staggered entrance animations**, hover effects with glow intensification, pulse animation on online status dots\n- **Fully mobile responsive** (1/2/3 column grid)\n\n**Key files:**\n- `SPEC.md` — full design spec\n- `src/lib/gateway.ts` — WebSocket + HTTP gateway client\n- `src/hooks/useAgentStatus.ts` — agent status polling hook\n- `src/components/` — all UI components\n\n**To run locally:**\n```bash\ncd /Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control\nnpm run dev\n```\nThen open `http://localhost:5173` (make sure the OpenClaw gateway is running on port 18789).\n\n**To deploy to Vercel:** connect the repo and it will auto-deploy from `dist/`. Set `VITE_GATEWAY_URL` env var to your LAN gateway address (e.g. `http://192.168.1.x:18789`) for remote access."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"